2. Theoretical background, literature review and research
hypotheses
This section outlines the theoretical channels and research hypoth-
eses through which AI technology innovation in banking and finance can
impact the financial performance of banks. Additionally, it offers a
synopsis of empirical research exploring the relationship between AI
technology innovation and banks’ financial performance.
2.1. Theoretical frameworks
In the dynamic landscape of global banking, understanding how AI
technology innovations reshape financial performance requires a
multifaceted approach: from leveraging unique AI capabilities as stra-
tegic resources (resource-based view), to tracing their diffusion patterns
across markets (diffusion of innovation theory), and navigating the
regulatory, ethical, and cultural landscapes shaping adoption (institu-
tional theory). The resource-based view (RBV) offers a theoretical lens to
understand how banking and finance artificial intelligence technology
innovation can influence banks’ financial performance. According to
RBV, firms gain competitive advantage and superior performance by
leveraging unique and valuable resources, such as AI capabilities, that
