3.3. Data and variables declaration
From 2010 to 2020, this research investigates the connection among
various factors, including bank return on assets (BROA), banking and
finance artificial intelligence technology innovation (BFAITI), bank non-
performing loans (BNPL), bank regulatory capital (BRC), economic
growth (GDPG), and government regulations (REG) across 20 econo-
mies. Additionally, the study delves into the moderating impact of
economic growth and the mediating role of ICT development (ICTD) on
the relationship between banking and finance AI technological innova-
tion (BFAITI) and banks’ financial performance (BROA). The chosen
sample and time frame were determined based on data availability for
the independent variable. Data related to all variables were extracted
from the Global Financial Development (GFD) and World Development
Indicators (WDI) within the World Bank database, as well as the Center
for Security and Emerging Technology (CSET) (Center for Security and
Emerging Technology, 2023a; World Bank, 2024). Table 1 presents a
description of the variables, including their measurement and source.
