3.3.4. Moderating variable
Economic growth (GDPG) measured by GDP growth can also moder-
ate the relationship between AI technology innovation and banks’
financial performance. Higher economic growth may amplify the posi-
tive impact of AI technology innovation on banks’ profitability, while
lower economic growth may dampen its effects (Banna & Alam, 2021).
3.3.5. Mediating variable
ICT Development (ICTD) measured by a composite of mobile cellular
subscriptions and individuals using the internet acts as a mediating
variable that explains the mechanism through which AI technology
innovation influences banks’ financial performance. Implementation of
AI technologies enhances ICT infrastructure development, leading to
improved operational efficiency and customer service quality, ulti-
mately affecting banks’ profitability (Shao, Lou, Wang, Mao, & Ye,
2022). The use of ICT variables including internet usage, mobile sub-
scriptions, and fixed telephone subscriptions have been employed in
several studies, especially banking and finance (Del Gaudio, Porzio,
Sampagnaro, & Verdoliva, 2021).
