show positive associations with BROA, suggesting that stronger regu-
latory capital and a conducive economic environment contribute to
improved financial performance. However, government regulations
exhibit a negative impact on BROA, highlighting the challenges imposed
by regulatory frameworks on banks’ profitability. Moreover, the inter-
action between BFAITI and economic growth highlights the importance
of coupling AI technology innovation with economic growth to maxi-
mize its positive impact on banks’ financial performance. Furthermore,
the mediation analysis illustrates that ICT development plays a crucial
role in mediating the relationship between BFAITI and banks’ financial
performance, indicating that the enhancement of ICT infrastructure fa-
cilitates the translation of AI technology innovation into improved
financial outcomes for banks. Considering the lagged effects of AI
technology innovation, the study reveals a dynamic relationship be-
tween BFAITI and banks’ financial performance over time. While an
initial surge in innovation leads to an immediate improvement in
financial performance, prolonged exposure to innovation costs or
diminishing benefits may result in a decline in performance over time.
Finally, the robustness analysis confirms the consistency and reliability
of the baseline findings, reinforcing the positive association between
BFAITI and banks’ financial performance across different methodologies
and measurement variables. This study highlights the significant role of
banking and finance AI technology innovation in boosting banks’
financial performance, while also emphasizing the necessity of inte-
grating contextual factors such as economic growth, regulatory frame-
works, and ICT development to fully leverage AI’s benefits. Notably, it
highlights a significant gap in the literature regarding the complex in-
teractions between these factors and AI adoption, calling for deeper
exploration to optimize strategic implementation in the banking sector.
Drawing from the findings outlined above, several policy implica-
tions can be suggested to harness the potential benefits of banking and
finance AI technology innovation while addressing associated chal-
lenges. First, there should be the promotion of AI innovation ecosystem.
Governments and regulatory bodies in the 20 countries should incen-
tivize and support the development of an AI innovation ecosystem
within the banking and finance sector. This includes funding research
and development initiatives, providing tax incentives for AI investment,
and fostering collaboration between financial institutions, technology
firms, and academic institutions. By doing so, policymakers can stimu-
late innovation, enhance the competitiveness of the banking sector, and
create an environment conducive to AI-driven growth. Second, regula-
tors need to update and adapt regulatory frameworks to accommodate
the rapid advancements in AI technology while ensuring consumer
protection, data privacy, and financial stability. This involves estab-
lishing clear guidelines for AI implementation in banking, conducting
regular audits of AI systems, and promoting transparency and explain-
able AI-driven decision-making processes. Such measures will help build
trust in AI systems, safeguard against potential risks, and ensure that AI
adoption aligns with regulatory standards. Third, policymakers should
prioritize investment in ICT infrastructure to support the adoption and
implementation of AI technologies in the banking sector. This includes
expanding broadband access, enhancing cybersecurity measures, and
promoting digital literacy among the population. Strengthening ICT
infrastructure is crucial for maximizing the benefits of AI technology and
ensuring that all stakeholders can effectively leverage AI capabilities.
Fourth, financial institutions should focus on improving risk manage-
ment practices and asset quality to mitigate the negative impact of non-
performing loans on financial performance. This may involve imple-
menting stricter lending standards, enhancing credit risk assessment
models using AI, and diversifying loan portfolios to reduce concentra-
tion risk. By adopting robust risk management strategies, banks can
enhance their resilience and stability in the face of economic fluctua-
tions. Fifth, governments should implement policies aimed at fostering
economic growth and promoting innovation synergy. This includes
promoting entrepreneurship, investing in education and skills
