E. Baffour Gyau et al. development in STEM fields, and facilitating collaboration between the
public and private sectors to leverage AI technology for economic
development. By aligning AI innovation with economic growth strate-
gies, countries can create a sustainable environment for AI adoption and
utilization. Sixth, financial institutions should adopt long-term strategic
planning approaches that account for the dynamic nature of AI tech-
nology innovation and its potential lagged effects on financial perfor-
mance. This involves conducting regular assessments of AI
implementation strategies, monitoring industry trends, and adjusting
business models accordingly. Strategic planning will enable banks to
stay ahead of technological advancements and continuously optimize
their AI-driven initiatives. Seventh, policymakers and regulators should
establish mechanisms for continuous monitoring and evaluation of AI
adoption in the banking sector. This ensures compliance with regula-
tions, assesses potential risks, and measures the effectiveness of AI-
driven initiatives in improving financial performance and customer
outcomes. Continuous monitoring will help maintain the integrity and
reliability of AI systems while fostering innovation. Lastly, international
collaboration and knowledge-sharing initiatives should be encouraged
to facilitate the exchange of best practices, lessons learned, and regu-
latory experiences related to AI adoption in the banking and finance
sector. Promoting global standards and frameworks for responsible AI
governance will foster innovation, enhance competitiveness, and ensure
that AI technology contributes to sustainable development goals. By
implementing these policy recommendations, stakeholders can effec-
tively leverage banking and finance AI technology innovation to drive
sustainable economic growth, enhance financial stability, and improve
the overall well-being of society. This study not only informs policy-
making in the 20 countries but also provides actionable insights for
practitioners, researchers, and global efforts toward achieving sustain-
able development goals.
The research has few limitations despite the valuable empirical dis-
coveries. Firstly, the investigation is confined to the period from 2010 to
2020, primarily due to constraints related to the dataset. Future research
endeavors could enhance comprehensiveness by extending the dataset
to incorporate more recent years. Secondly, this study focuses on the
moderating influence of economic growth; however, forthcoming
research should contemplate additional factors that might play a
moderating role. Thirdly, expanding the scope to encompass a more
extensive array of countries, provided there is available data, could
provide a more detailed understanding of the connections. Lastly, up-
coming research endeavors could derive benefits from undertaking
heterogeneous analyses, taking into account factors like the income
levels or developmental statuses of countries.
